uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.util
Class SitewiseSpecificLikelihoodSupportAaml

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.qmul.sbcs.evolution.convergence.util.SitewiseSpecificLikelihoodSupportAaml
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
public class SitewiseSpecificLikelihoodSupportAaml
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable

Since:
r130 12/3/2013 Class to contain basically all the SSLS features required.

Designed to be initialised with ASR;
SSLS patterns loaded;
other aaml run parameters (model; overall lnL, alpha, fitted tree, li etc) loaded from parsed aaml.out file;
ÆSSLS calculated from patterns;
serialised and reinflated as object afterwards (UNTESTED) (e.g. downloaded...)

IMPORTANT: One model (Aaml run) per object.......

Author:
joeparker
